<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFE0FFD0FCD62B45F08BFF25" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="317" pageId="23" pageNumber="312" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFE0FFD0FCD62B45F08BFF25" blockId="23.[828,1437,1115,2067]" lastBlockId="28.[151,761,190,693]" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="317" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE0FFDBFCD62B45F2A1FBA3" bold="true" box="[828,944,1115,1139]" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae brown. Antennomere II longer than III. Pronotum with smoky stripe reaching posterior margin. Thoracic and abdominal pleurites and sternites with black spots (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE0FFDBFC282BA2F506FB03" box="[962,1047,1212,1235]" captionStart="Figs 5" captionStartId="6.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[248,1334,197,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 5A–F.Dorsal and ventral surface.A–B – Hypoxys servillei sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys venustus sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177537/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
). Anterior excavation of metasternal process harboring fourth and almost whole third rostral segment (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE0FFDBFC402BE2F501FAC3" box="[938,1040,1276,1299]" captionStart="Figs 19" captionStartId="25.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[176,1410,204,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-16@25.[176,1410,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 19A–F. Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Arrow indicates expansion of the ventral rim with a lateral excavation. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177563/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Fig. 19F</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE0FFDBFBCD2BE5F5C6FAC3" bold="true" box="[1063,1239,1275,1299]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygophore (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE0FFDBFA812BE2F29FFAE3" captionStart="Figs 19" captionStartId="25.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[176,1410,204,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-16@25.[176,1410,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 19A–F. Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Arrow indicates expansion of the ventral rim with a lateral excavation. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177563/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Figs 19A–D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal rim with small round projections adjacent to posterolateral angle (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE0FFDBFBAA2A22F5B7FA83" box="[1088,1190,1340,1363]" captionStart="Figs 19" captionStartId="25.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[176,1410,204,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-16@25.[176,1410,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 19A–F. Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Arrow indicates expansion of the ventral rim with a lateral excavation. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177563/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Fig. 19A</figureCitation>
). Posterolateral angles developed, bent inwards, acuminate (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE0FFDBFB202A42F43CFAA3" box="[1226,1325,1372,1395]" captionStart="Figs 19" captionStartId="25.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[176,1410,204,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-16@25.[176,1410,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 19A–F. Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Arrow indicates expansion of the ventral rim with a lateral excavation. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177563/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Fig. 19A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup trilobate, curved, elongated, concave medially, parallel to dorsal rim and almost reaching apex of posterolateral angle; inner part bifid, forming two long digitiform lobes; outer part tongue-like (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE0FFDBFAE32AC2F49EFA23" box="[1289,1423,1500,1523]" captionStart="Figs 19" captionStartId="25.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[176,1410,204,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-16@25.[176,1410,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 19A–F. Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Arrow indicates expansion of the ventral rim with a lateral excavation. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177563/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Figs 19C,D</figureCitation>
). Paramere with two lobes; anterior lobe square, developed and directed to dorsal rim; lateral lobe small and rounded (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE0FFDBFCA92922F2D4F983" box="[835,965,1596,1619]" captionStart="Figs 19" captionStartId="25.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[176,1410,204,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-16@25.[176,1410,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 19A–F. Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Arrow indicates expansion of the ventral rim with a lateral excavation. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177563/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Figs 19C,D</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with crown of long, dense setae on lateral excavation; posterior face subpentagonal (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE0FFDBFA872942F297F943" captionStart="Figs 19" captionStartId="25.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[176,1410,204,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-16@25.[176,1410,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 19A–F. Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Arrow indicates expansion of the ventral rim with a lateral excavation. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177563/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Figs 19C,D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with expansions acuminate, large, ventrolateral side broadly excavated, dorsal side without brown spot; almost level with posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE0FFDBFA8729A2F296F923" captionStart="Figs 19" captionStartId="25.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[176,1410,204,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-16@25.[176,1410,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 19A–F. Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Arrow indicates expansion of the ventral rim with a lateral excavation. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177563/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Figs 19B,C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE0FFDBFC7429C5F57AF923" bold="true" box="[926,1131,1755,1779]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Genital plates (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE0FFDBFACD29C2F481F923" box="[1319,1424,1756,1779]" captionStart="Figs 19" captionStartId="25.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[176,1410,204,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-16@25.[176,1410,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs 19A–F. Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Arrow indicates expansion of the ventral rim with a lateral excavation. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177563/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Fig. 19E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 posterior margin with posterolateral angles dentiform and posteriorly directed, inner angle dentiform and projected to valvifers 9; imaginary line tangent to posterolateral angles not reaching distal margin of valvifers 9; inner margin slightly projected posteriorly, leaving bottom of excavation convex; excavation in U-shaped. Valvulae 8 not visible. Apices of laterotergites 8 clearly above level of apices of abdominal segment VII. Laterotergites 9 slightly surpassing band connecting laterotergites 8; apices clearly below imaginary line tangent to apices of abdominal segment VII.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
